    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix deadlock in UE tracer GUI event handling\n\n### Summary\nThe UE tracer application was experiencing deadlocks when users interacted with the event selector GUI while trace events were being processed. This occurred because the main event processing thread held the ue_data lock while calling handle_event(), which could trigger GUI updates requiring the GUI lock, while simultaneously the GUI thread held the GUI lock and tried to acquire the ue_data lock through is_on_changed().\n\nThis fix modifies the event loop to release the data lock before calling handle_event, preventing the inconsistent lock acquisition ordering that caused the deadlock.\n\n### Changes\n- `common/utils/T/tracer/ue.c`: Modified event loop to release ue_data lock before calling handle_event\n- `common/utils/T/tracer/enb.c`: Applied same fix to prevent identical deadlock issue  \n- `common/utils/T/tracer/gnb.c`: Applied same fix to prevent identical deadlock issue\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the original deadlock:\n1. Start the UE tracer with a database file\n2. Connect to a running UE instance\n3. Rapidly toggle event selections in the event selector window while trace events are being received\n4. The application will eventually freeze with both threads blocked waiting for each other's locks\n\nAfter this fix, the same scenario works without deadlocks as the lock acquisition order is now consistent.\n"
}